  </advanced_techniques>

  <detection>
    - Audit CSP headers regularly
    - Check for JSONP endpoints on allowed origins
    - Review for Angular/framework gadgets
    - Test for base-uri restrictions
    - Monitor CSP violation reports
  </detection>

  <validation>
    - Identify weak directives in CSP
    - Successfully bypass CSP with gadgets
    - Execute JavaScript despite CSP
    - Exfiltrate data using dangling markup
    - Document full attack chain
  </validation>

  <pro_tips>
    - Always check CSP Evaluator for quick wins
    - JSONP endpoints are the most common bypass vector
    - 'strict-dynamic' is not foolproof - check script loaders
    - Missing base-uri + relative script paths = easy bypass
    - Even report-only CSP indicates security awareness
    - Combine DOM XSS + CSP bypass for stored impact
  </pro_tips>

  <remember>CSP bypasses transform "mitigated" XSS into exploitable vulnerabilities. The best CSP bypass hunters maintain a list of JSONP endpoints and script gadgets for commonly allowed domains. A strict CSP only works if every allowed origin is secure - one vulnerable JSONP endpoint breaks the entire policy.</remember>
</vulnerability_guide>
